the supremecourtph in gr no 277540 balintay v comelec has granted the petition of chito bulatao balintay a member of the indigenous peoples of zambales reversing the comelec resolution that rejected his certificate of candidacy coc for zambales governor in the 2025 elections balintay filed his coc on the last day of filing 25 minutes prior to the closing time
but since his coc was incomplete missing a required fifth copy

and documentary stamps he was advised to complete his documents he returned 3 minutes past the 500 pm deadline the comelec rejected his coc citing section 37 of comelec resolution no 11045 the sc ruled that the comelec gravely abused its discretion when it did not allow balintay to file his coc it held that the comelec should reexamine whether its rules serve the interest of justice
and fair play the sc ordered the comelec to accept balintays coc

and include his name in the official ballots for zambales governor in the 2025 elections the sc on january 14 2025 had issued a temporary restraining order tro preventing the comelec from enforcing its decision rejecting balintays application read the full text of the press briefer

comelec vs respicio defending democracy or silencing critics
so comelec just filed a cyber libel case against isabela vice mayoral candidate atty jeryll harold respicio for claiming that votecounting machines vcms can be manipulated
and that backroom programs can alter election results on one hand comelec wants to protect the credibility of elections
and thats a fight worth taking on the other are they trying to stop misinformation
or shutting down a critic by the way hes a critic

and not a hater haters dont criticize they hate 247 lets break it down why comelect has a point election disinformation is dangerous fake claims can erode public trust if people think elections are rigged before a single vote is cast why should we even bother voting comelec has to defend itself if they just let baseless accusations slide they allow the idea that the electoral process is a scam legal action has its place if respicio lied
then yes he should be held accountable spreading false information
especially about elections is reckless
but lets not pretend this is a simple openandshut case why comelecs action is concerning shutting down critics isnt the same as proving them wrong why is comelecs first move a lawsuit
instead of a public clarification
instead of threatening legal action why not invite independent audits demonstrate safeguards
and let facts speak for themselves this is a dangerous precedent disinformation is a problem
so is the government punishing critics
especially when the case involves disqualification disbarment
and revoking his cpa license is this about election integrity
or sending a message to anyone who dares to challenge the system what if theres even a sliver of truth if atty respicio has zero evidence he deserves to be called out
but what if theres something worth looking into filing cases
instead of addressing concerns only fuels more doubt heres the problem atty respicio made bold claims without evidence if youre going to say the system is rigged you better come with solid proof

otherwise youre just adding to the noise comelecs response to me feels like overkill a libel case a disqualification case a disbarment case a license revocation thats not just holding someone accountable thats obliterating them this could have been handled better comelec should have challenged atty respicio to provide proof if none exists debunk it with facts atty respicio should have backed up his claims
or explicitly claimed he was just speculating both sides should have engaged in a discussion

instead of launching into legal warfare unlike fake news peddlers atty respicio was trying to point out an issue with the vcm machines worth looking into comelec should have proven atty respicio wrong by presenting facts
and accountability suing a vice mayoral candidate doesnt restore trust in elections
but debunking his claims that just might

and action this is a significant moment for us not just as a political organization
but as a team that has consistently worked to move the country forward romualdez said as lakascmd president he highlighted the partys history of producing two presidents
and shaping key policies that strengthened the economy improved national security

and built critical infrastructure we have always believed that leadership is about producing real results not just holding positions he added romualdez emphasized that lakascmds dominant status comes with the responsibility of advancing the bagong pilipinas agenda ensuring efficient governance inclusive economic growth

and public trust in institutions this recognition carries even greater weight bagong pilipinas is about transformationabout making government work more efficiently ensuring that economic growth is felt by ordinary filipinos
and restoring trust in public institutions he stated he
also underscored the partys role in safeguarding electoral integrity vowing to help ensure clean credible
and orderly elections in 2025 this is more than just a title it is a call to work harder to serve better
and to prove once again that lakascmd is not just a party of influence it is a party of action romualdez stressed

yet now you do the same these actions are

also very sporadic not part of regular engagement making him seem patronizing bordering on poverty porn the masses interpret it as you think were easily won over by gimmicks we see through your insincerity the disconnect reinforces a class divide with elite politicians slumming it for votes which feels insulting to voters who crave genuine connection kiko an experienced former senator could leverage his track record
instead of prioritizing gimmicks this strategic inconsistency switching between substance

and shallow tactics exposes a lack of authenticity voters distrust politicians who shift strategies abruptly perceiving it opportunism rather than principled leadership this happened to leni who was initially packaged as the best lawyer in the universe to a lawyer na naghahadouken from a serious economist to a comedian doing a skit with kiko the masses reject performative gestures responding with ridicule this reflects a broader demand for respect
and dignity in political engagement authenticity trumps theatrics theatrics is acceptable for candidates who have nothing to offer but entertainment
but for experienced former senator like kiko the focus should be policy achievements rather than random political stunts
